It's reported MI6, which deals with global intelligence, wants hundreds of recruits and has made its first-ever cinema advert. LONDON - British spy agency MI6 is embarking on a major campaign to recruit more officers, particularly from minority groups.It's reported the agency, which deals with global intelligence, wants hundreds of new recruits and has made its first-ever cinema advert.The push comes as authorities face a growing threat in global terrorism and increased attacks in cyberspace.What began with a strategic newspaper interviews has now turn into a full-blown campaign.MI6, formerly known as a secret intelligent service, says it s responding to a changing world.Typecast by the James Bond movie, the agency says what it s not looking for is another 007.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)